          <article id="analyze-and-monitor-data" class="source-article">
            <header>
              <h2>Analyze & monitor data</h2>
              <p>Sign up to receive tree clearing alerts for the humid tropical forest biome. Tree clearing alerts indicate areas where tree cover loss is likely to have recently occurred, based off of an analysis of satellite imagery and complimentary data on forest fires and weather events. To learn more about this data set and where it applies, please visit the data page.</p>
              <p>When you sign up to receive alerts for an area of interest, you will be notified when a new tree clearing has been detected, as often as every 30 days. Once you identify the area you would like to monitor, simply enter your email address to subscribe to alerts.</p>
              <p><strong>Interested in monitoring tree clearing alerts in commodities? Visit <a href='http://www.commodities.globalforestwatch.org' target='_blank'>GFW Commodities</a></strong>.</p>
            </header>
            <ul class='sources'>
              <li class='source-item first'>
                <div class='source_header'>
                  <strong class='source_title'>Subscribe to alerts for a hand-drawn area on the map</strong>
                  <i class='expand_arrow'></i>
                </div>
                <div class='source_body'>
                  <div class='source_summary'>
                    <p>1. Click the button below to enter the map with the analysis tool activated.
                    <p>2. Draw a shape within the humid tropical forest biome (the area shaded in pink) and click “Analyze.”</p>
                    <p>3. Once the results window appears, click the “mail” icon located at the bottom.</p>
                    <a href="/map/3/15.00/27.00/ALL/grayscale/forma?begin=2006-01-01&end=2014-10-31" class="btn gray medium uppercase">Draw an area</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
